    "body": "You are requesting the balance for address `0xe41530b5f0a30b13cb027b94812f91742f3557d2`, at blocknumber `12M` \r\n```\r\n>>> 0xB8F3A7\r\n12120999\r\n```\r\nThe stateroot for that block is `0x48fb5a41730d3101690d40e3933e55e6351c46a20de7cbdf9bb3a1ddadf107f8` (https://etherscan.io/block/12120999), so geth tries to look it up. However: \r\n```\r\n\"missing trie node 48fb5a41730d3101690d40e3933e55e6351c46a20de7cbdf9bb3a1ddadf107f8 (path ) \"\r\n```\r\nYou do not have the state for block `12120999`. This is to be expected, a snap-synced node will only ever have the most recent state, after the \"pivot point\" around the time the sync was performed. \r\n",
